 Assignment 2: IDE Selection

Choose one of the following Python Integrated Development Environments (IDEs): 

- Visual Studio Code (VS Code)
- Jupyter Notebook

Follow the steps below to install the selected IDE on your computer:

Option 1: Visual Studio Code (VS Code)

1. Download VS Code:
   - Visit the [Visual Studio Code website](https://code.visualstudio.com/).
   - Download the installer for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).

2.Install VS Code:
   - Run the downloaded installer and follow the installation instructions.
   - On Windows, ensure to select the option to add VS Code to your PATH during the installation process.

3. Set Up Python Extension:
   - Open VS Code.
   - Go to the Extensions view by clicking on the Extensions icon in the Activity Bar on the side of the window or by pressing `Ctrl+Shift+X`.
   - Search for "Python" and install the official Python extension by Microsoft.
   - Once installed, reload VS Code to activate the extension.

 Option 2: Jupyter Notebook

1. Install Anaconda Distribution:
   - Visit the [Anaconda website](https://www.anaconda.com/products/distribution).
   - Download the installer for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).

2. Install Anaconda:
   - Run the downloaded installer and follow the installation instructions.
   - Ensure to select the option to add Anaconda to your PATH during the installation process (on Windows).

3. Launch Jupyter Notebook:
   - Open the Anaconda Navigator application.
   - Click on the "Launch" button under the Jupyter Notebook section.
   - A new tab will open in your default web browser with the Jupyter Notebook interface.

